	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In most Adobe software, those kinds of collapsible, dockable panels are called &quot;palettes&quot;. When I first heard the term, I got confused because I thought &quot;palette&quot; was supposed to mean &quot;discrete collection of colors&quot;, but nope, it apparently can refer to those panels. They later changed the name to something else, so I guess I wasn't the only one getting confused. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /><br /><br />It seems that they can be called dockable panes, panels, windows, etc. The key word being &quot;dockable&quot;.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

